{"lemma":"عَرْكُ","slug":"عَرْكُ","root":"ع.ر.ك","root_slug":"ع-ر-ك","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ر-ك","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28806","n28807","n28808"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to knead, to mix thoroughly until cohesive"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to rub, to chafe, to wear out by rubbing"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.ra.ka/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28806","headword_ar":"عَرْكٌ","root":"Erk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [originally an inf. n.,] accord. to El- 'Adebbes El-Kinánee,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAz~N","text_ar":"حَازٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An incision,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cut, made by the elbow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the arm,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[probably a mistake for"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1, near the middle of the paragraph,)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so as to reach to the flesh, cutting through the skin, by the side of the callous protuberance upon the breast."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAz~N","text_ar":"حَازٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hz","text_ar":"حز"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-  [Hence, app.,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earokayoni","text_ar":"عَرْكَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as used by a poet, [the dual, it seems, being put for the sing. for the sake of the rhyme, as it ends a verse,] is a metaphorical term for The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vulva"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman; the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earok","text_ar":"عَرْك"},{"kind":"text","text":"in its primary sense being in the camel. (TA.)       -A2-  Also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dung"},{"kind":"text","text":"of beasts or birds of prey. (O, K.)       -A3-  And Herbage"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trodden and eaten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n28807","headword_ar":"عَرَكٌ","root":"Erk","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fishermen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, MA, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakapN","text_ar":"عَرَكَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (MA; [but this I do not find elsewhere;]) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwkN","text_ar":"عُرُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, K:) one of whom is called ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakiY~N","text_ar":"عَرَكِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AA, S, MA, O, K,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fisherman who holds in his hand an iron implement having five prongs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(MA:)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakN","text_ar":"عَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakiY~N","text_ar":"عَرَكِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"being like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarabN","text_ar":"عَرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarabiY~N","text_ar":"عَرَبِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AA, S, O:) [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakiY~N","text_ar":"عَرَكِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the n. un.:] accord. to the K,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakN","text_ar":"عَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwkN","text_ar":"عُرُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are pls. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakiY~N","text_ar":"عَرَكِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but IAth says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuruwkN","text_ar":"عُرُوكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakN","text_ar":"عَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakN","text_ar":"عَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sailors,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mariners,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, S, O, K,) because they fish, not as being [properly] a name for them: (AA, S, O:) Zuheyr says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"tago$aY AlHudaApu bihimo Hur~a Alkaviybi kamaA\n                      \n                     \n                        yugo$iY Als~afaAy^ina mawoja All~uj~api AlEaraku"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camel-drivers cover with them the middle of the elevated expanse of sand like as the seamen cause the waves of the deep to cover the ships"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but AO related this verse otherwise, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mawoju","text_ar":"مَوْجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the nom. case, and making"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaraku","text_ar":"العَرَكُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to be an epithet applied to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mwj","text_ar":"موج"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmutalaATim","text_ar":"المُتَلَاطِم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though the meaning were,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like as the colliding waves of the deep cover the ships"},{"kind":"text","text":"with their surf]. (S, O.)       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawotN","text_ar":"صَوْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A sound, noise, voice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarikN","text_ar":"عَرِكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K.)       -A3-  It is also the subst. denoted by the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earaka AlA_ibila fiY AlHamoDi","text_ar":"عَرَكَ الاـِبِلَ فِى الحَمْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v., app. as meaning The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"act of leaving camels amid the pasturage termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to obtain thereof what they want;"},{"kind":"text","text":"a meaning given in the O as an explanation of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakorakN","text_ar":"عَرَكْرَكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is perhaps in this instance a mistranscription]. (K.)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2024}],"source_refs":["O","K","AA","S","MA","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n28808","headword_ar":"عَرِكٌ","root":"Erk","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who throws down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostrates, his antagonists much,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"often;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sir~iyEN","text_ar":"صِرِّيعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O;) in the K and in some of the copies of the S"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SariyE","text_ar":"صَرِيع"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amiyr","text_ar":"اَمِير"},{"kind":"text","text":"; [which is app. a mistranscription;] (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in striving, contending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflicting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in might, courage, valour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prowess,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"battle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in altercation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaArikN","text_ar":"مُعَارِكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) pl. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Earikuwna","text_ar":"عَرِكُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, K, TA: in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarikuwA","text_ar":"عَرِكُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolN EarikN","text_ar":"رَمْلٌ عَرِكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEoraworikN","text_ar":"مُعْرَوْرِكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sands, intermingling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EariykN","text_ar":"عَرِيكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, TA,) which last epithet is erroneously applied in the K to the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"instead of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ramolN","text_ar":"رَمْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as is also in one instance ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEoraworikN","text_ar":"مُعْرَوْرِكٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK in this latter instance written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEoraworakN","text_ar":"مُعْرَوْرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EarakN","text_ar":"عَرَكٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","L"]}]}}